Name: extrapulmonary tuberculosis
Definition: A tuberculosis that occurs at body sites other than the lung.

Name: cardiac tuberculosis
Definition: An osteochondrodysplasia that is characterized by congenital hypertrichosis

Name: multidrug-resistant tuberculosis
Definition: A tuberculosis that is resistant to isoniazid and rifampicin
Synonym: Urothelial carcinoma of the renal Pelvis and Ureter

Name: obsolete renal pelvis and ureter cancer
Definition: A tuberculosis that is resistant to isoniazid and rifampicin
Synonym: Urothelial carcinoma of the renal Pelvis and Ureter
